Adebayo Obajemu Cadbury Nigeria Plc on Wednesday published its Fourth Quarter report for the period ended, 31 December 2022. The result shows growth in the companyâ€™s topline and bottom line figures, year on year. A turnover of N55.21 billion was reported for the 12 months period, up by 30.30% from N42.37 billion reported the previous year. Profit after tax grew year on year by 110.38% to N946 million from N449.7 million reported the previous year. Earnings per share of the company stand at N0.50, up by 110.38% from the EPS of N0.24 achieved the previous year. At the share price of N11.85, the P/E ratio of Cadbury stands at 23.52x with earnings yield of 4.25%.